President Trump visited Midland, Texas to celebrate the achievements of the energy industry and to send a message to those trying to shut it down. He praised the hardworking citizens of the industry and emphasized that the United States is now the number one energy superpower. He promised to defend American energy independence and not be reliant on foreign suppliers. He also provided an update on the battle against the COVID-19 pandemic and highlighted his administration's efforts to develop vaccines. The President thanked Double Eagle Energy for hosting the event and signed permits for pipeline and railway infrastructure on the nation's border. He criticized the radical left and their agenda to destroy the oil and gas industries, stating that their policies would lead to the death of American prosperity and the end of the American middle class. He also highlighted the environmental protections implemented under his administration and the job creation in the energy sector. The President concluded by expressing his commitment to always put America first and to never let Texas down.